The paper discusses model-based reinforcement learning (MBRL) with a focus on uncertainty-aware methods. This topic is closely related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as well as robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY). The paper also mentions simulated robotics tasks, which suggests a potential connection to computer vision (cs.CV) for generating and analyzing simulated environments.
